It is failing constantly for my PR as well - https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/11751/overview/bbcb1d49-f632-473d-9391-[â€¦]roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1&ts=1719483424501.3&att=1 (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/11751/overview/bbcb1d49-f632-473d-9391-38f0f6bdd0c9/replay?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1&ts=1719483424501.3&att=1)

By looking at the trace CJ shared, I am seeing the below error which is coming as for the value of custom_request a string is being sent from here (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/f4318083bee3d5fcfd0fea829dd7b9e5ffa3afaf/distributed-tasks/celery/app-tasks/src/py/instabase/tasks/apps/aihub_builder_util.py#L395-L402).
```  File "/instabase/workers/celery-app-tasks/py/instabase/aihub_utils/aihub_apps_util.py", line 875, in call_ibllm
    custom_request["source_id"] = metrics_params["source_id"]

TypeError: 'str' object does not support item assignment```
@Vishnu It looks like in this (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/58875/files#diff-23ca21e1b7a8fde91f5232c2730b80344f548e83e085f5ec8eb405d64d748e63R857-R861) PR some reorg of params was done for `call_ibllm` where ibdoc_path was moved as 3rd arg and from the above shared code (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/f4318083bee3d5fcfd0fea829dd7b9e5ffa3afaf/distributed-tasks/celery/app-tasks/src/py/instabase/tasks/apps/aihub_builder_util.py#L395-L402) it's being sent as a positional param instead of a named param, hence the failure. Could you take a look?
@Vasu thanks for the catch, pushing a fix
@Vishnu can you merge this soon so that it makes it into the next crafting deployment to fix our cypress tests? :pray:
@Jessica @CJ should we push a re-deploy on crafting-cyp ?
nvm looks like a re-deploy is already happening
